<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4590557>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Maraura macracantha (Smirnov and Timms, 1983) from Lake Numalla, Queensland, Australia, collected by B. V. Timms in April 2002. Parthenogenetic female: (A) lateral view; (B) ventral margin of valves; (C) anterior part of head shield with outline of antennula; (D, E) postabdomen; (F) dorsal margin of postabdomen; (G) postabdominal claw; (H) antenna; (I) maxilla. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for A–E and H; 0.05 mm for F, G and I." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4590557/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4590561>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Maraura macracantha (Smirnov and Timms, 1983) from Lake Numalla, Queensland, Australia collected by B. V. Timms in April 2002. Parthenogenetic female: (A) lateral view; (B) head in ventrolateral view; (C) head shield; (D) head pores (position of lateral pore is indicated by the arrow); (E) major head pores; (F) postabdomen in ventrolateral view; (G) distal part of postabdomen; (H) antenna. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for A; 0.05 mm for B, C and F; 0.02 mm for D, G and H; 0.01 mm for E." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4590561/files/figure.png" .

